Like _wabi_ and _sabi_, synonyms for Japanese aesthetic sensibilities, _yurui_ evades ready translation. The best way to comprehend the term is to place it along the extended lineage of words such as _aware_ (sensitivity or subjective emotion) and _okashi_ (emotional attraction), which appeal to human emotion.

